hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Apply the Hadamard gate to the initial state:
$$|\psi_1\rangle = H|\psi_0\rangle
= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}1 & 1\\1 & -1\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}1\\0\end{pmatrix}
= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}1\\1\end{pmatrix}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\bigl(|0\rangle+|1\rangle\bigr)\,. $$

2. Apply the phase gate $P(\pi/2)$:
$$|\psi_f\rangle = P\!\bigl(\tfrac\pi2\bigr)|\psi_1\rangle
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}1&0\\0&e^{i\pi/2}\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}1\\1\end{pmatrix}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}1\\e^{i\pi/2}\end{pmatrix}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}1\\i\end{pmatrix}\,. $$

3. Compute the expectation value of $Y$:
$$Y|\psi_f\rangle
=\begin{pmatrix}0&-i\\i&0\end{pmatrix}
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}1\\i\end{pmatrix}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}-i\cdot i\\i\cdot1\end{pmatrix}
=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\begin{pmatrix}1\\i\end{pmatrix}
=|\psi_f\rangle\,. $$

Hence
$$\langle Y\rangle
=\langle\psi_f|Y|\psi_f\rangle
=\langle\psi_f|\psi_f\rangle
=1\,. $$
